### Debounce Function
A debounce function delays the execution of a provided callback until after a specified wait time has passed since the last invocation, preventing excessive calls in rapid succession (e.g., during user input events).

```javascript
function debounce(func, delay) {
  let timeoutId;
  return function (...args) {
    clearTimeout(timeoutId);
    timeoutId = setTimeout(() => func.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}
```

### Example Usage
```javascript
// Debounce a search function to run only after user stops typing for 300ms
const searchInput = document.getElementById('search');
const debouncedSearch = debounce((query) => {
  console.log(`Searching for: ${query}`);
}, 300);

searchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
  debouncedSearch(e.target.value);
});
```
